You are building "직관생활" - a KBO baseball game attendance recording + Instagram card generator web app (PWA).

## Key Context
- Target users: Korean women aged 20-30 who are KBO baseball fans
- Core flow: Record game → Generate pretty card → Share to Instagram story
- Tech: Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Supabase
- Mobile-first PWA design
- Pastel color scheme (soft, feminine aesthetic)

## Code Style
- Always use TypeScript with strict types
- Use functional components with React hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling (no CSS modules, minimal inline styles)
- File names: kebab-case (e.g., pastel-card.tsx)
- Component names: PascalCase (e.g., PastelCard)
- Korean comments are acceptable
- Always handle loading and error states
- Use 'use client' directive only when needed (prefer Server Components)

## Design Rules
- Mobile-first: design for 375px width first
- Rounded corners: use rounded-xl or rounded-2xl
- Colors: use team pastel colors, not raw team colors
- Font: use system font stack (Pretendard if available)
- Card templates: always 9:16 ratio (1080x1920px for export)
- No KBO logos, mascots, or emblems - only team color codes
- Custom mascot character only (no team-specific animals)

## Architecture
- Refer to CLAUDE.md for full project structure and data models
- Use Supabase client from lib/supabase.ts
- API routes in app/api/ for server-side operations
- Team data from lib/teams.ts (constants, no hardcoding)

## When generating components:
1. Always check CLAUDE.md for data types and team codes
2. Use the TEAMS constant for colors, never hardcode team colors
3. Handle both landscape and portrait photo orientations
4. Card components must support dynamic team color theming
5. All user-facing text in Korean
